//Mass/Tumor - Characterization II - I describe


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button in 'CM reinforced' box in Page 03
And	I'm on Page 08 of Cardio MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Mass/Tumor' from the dropdown menu

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Yes' radio button is enabled in Early Gd-Enhancement (EGE)
And 'No' radio button is enabled in Early Gd-Enhancement (EGE)

And 'Yes' radio button is enabled in Late Gd-Enhancement (LGE)
And 'No' radio button is enabled in Late Gd-Enhancement (LGE)

And 'Bleeding' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fat signal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hyperintensity in STIR' checkbox is enabled

And 'Valve associated' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration through different tissue layers' checkbox is enabled

And 'Pericardial effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pleural effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Superimposed thrombus' checkbox is enabled

And 'None' radio button is enabled
And 'Mild' radio button is enabled
And 'High' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Yes' radio button in Early Gd-Enhancement (EGE)
Then 'Marked' radio button is enabled
And 'Mild' radio button is enabled
And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Yes' radio button in Late Gd-Enhancement (LGE)
Then 'Marked' radio button is enabled
And 'Mild' radio button is enabled
And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Pericardial effusion' checkbox
Then 'Haemorrhagic' checkbox is enabled
